      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOLO MAN (1) filled the minor money two on end before breaking through for a deserved win last time, scoring at Murray Bridge over 395m (22.10). Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Can make it two on the bounce. AFIRE (8) has an excellent record over this course and distance having never missed the placings in five starts, including two wins and three placings. In the money last time at Murray Bridge (16.93) in a Grade 5, finishing a 6 length second. With even luck and a clean start should be around the money. FEDERAL LADY (2) ran good time (31.07) winning a Grade 6 three back at Gawler but missed the frame latest finishing fourth at Gawler. Can turn it around this time. DIVERGENCE (6) warrants respect following a recent placing.",
